    bibo:volume "43" ;
    dc:creator "Gearner, Olivia M.; Philips, T. Keith" ;
    dc:date "2021" ;
    dc:title "Notaferrum n. gen. (Coleoptera: Ptinidae): the first known spider beetle associated with weaver ants" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4464308>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4464310>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4464316>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4464312> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4464308>
    dc:description "FIG. 1. — Dorsal and lateral views of Notaferrum natalensis (Pic, 1906) n. gen., n. comb.: A, type specimen of Ptinus natalensis Pic, 1906; B, specimen from Sodwana Bay Campground showing some of the variability of recumbent white setae on the elytra; C, specimen from Charters Creek, St. Lucia in lateral view showing the distinct blade-like structures on the pronotum; D, male genitalia. Scale bars: A-C, 1 mm; D, 100 μm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4464308/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4464310>
    dc:description "FIG. 2. — Close-up view of head and pronotum of Notaferrum natalensis (Pic, 1906) n. gen., n. comb.: A, dorsal view; B, frontal view. Note the distinct lateral and dorsal trichomes (see arrows)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4464310/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4464316>
    dc:description "FIG. 4. — Distribution of Notaferrum natalensis (Pic, 1906) n. gen., n. comb. based on three known specimens, South Africa, Kwa-Zulu Natal Province." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4464316/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4464312>
    dc:description "FIG. 3. — Ventral surface of Notaferrum natalensis (Pic, 1906) n. gen., n. comb. and host ant Oecophylla longinoda Latreille, 1802: A, ventral surface showing the apically expanded prosternal process that extends beyond the procoxae (see arrow), very reduced length of the fourth abdominal ventrite, and the small depression (devoid of setae) on the metaventrite near the posterior margin; B, host ant specimen, Oecophylla longinoda Latreille, 1802, associated with the specimen from St. Lucia, SANC. Scale bar: 2 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4464312/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

